definition.value: A halophenol that is any phenol containing one or more covalently bonded chlorine atoms.
An inorganic nitrate salt having zinc(2+) as the couterion.
The inorganic nitrate salt of gallium.
An organogermanium compound that is germanium which carries four methyl groups.
A monocarboxylic acid anion obtained by deprotonation of the carboxy group of any chlorophenoxyacetic acid.
The inorganic nitrate salt of caesium.
A methylbenzyl alcohol that is benzyl alcohol substituted by methyl groups at positions 2 and 4.
A methylbenzyl alcohol that is benzyl alcohol substituted by methyl groups at positions 3 and 4.
A methylbenzyl alcohol that is benzyl alcohol substituted by methyl groups at positions 3 and 5.
A member of the class of benzyl alcohols in which the hydrogen at position 4 on the phenyl ring of benzyl alcohol has been replaced by an ethyl group.
A monocarboxylic acid that is phenoxyacetic acid in which at least one of the phenyl hydrogens is replaced by chlorine.
A member of the class of benzaldehydes that is benzaldehyde substituted by methyl groups at positions 3 and 5, respectively.
An N(6)-acyl-L-lysine residue that has (S)-lactoyl as the N(6)-acyl group.
A deuterated compound that is tetramethylsilane in which the twelve hydrogens are replaced by deuterium.
Any  chlorohydrocarbon that is phenylethane substituted by at least one chloro group at unspecified position.
A nucleoside phosphate that is derived from a nucleotide.
